        <item>
            <title>
[QLSP-324] iPOS-Disable cash drawer functionality if receipt printer switch is off
</title>
            <link>https://idevtools.cfahome.com/jira/browse/QLSP-324</link>
            <project id="11405" key="QLSP">Quality ServicePoint</project>
            <description>
                <p>Disable cash drawer functionality if receipt printer switch is off is an enhancement for R4 2017. There is no BRS, therefore, this test is written on knowledge of prior iPOS experience and WIT 423737. </p>
                <p>This test case covers the verification of new functionality added for this enhancement, denoted by the f in the title. </p>
                <p>WIT Description: Prevent cash drawer functionality if the receipt printer toggle switch under iPOS Setup is turned off. Cash drawer relies on the printer connection for functionality, so without the printer switch on, cash drawer should never work.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Functionality to be verified:</li>
                    <li>Disabling the receipt printer disables the switch for cash drawer and disables all functionality for the cash drawer</li>
                    <li>Cash drawer can not be enabled while receipt printer is not enabled</li>
                    <li>Receipt printer can or cannot be disabled/enabled while the user is signed in?</li>
                    <li>Re-enable receipt printer? Does it auto re-enable the cash drawer? The assumption is no.</li>
                    <li>Cash drawer and receipt printer connectivity - Loss of connection, reconnect, pair when enabled,</li>
                    <li>Cash drawer Status updates</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    <b>Preconditions:</b>
                    <br/> Epson TM88V Paired to the iPad. Cash drawer plugged into the connected receipt printer. All setup switches are disabled.
                </p>
            </description>
